To generate a table of contents (TOC) automatically in a LaTeX document, you can use the `hyperref` package. Here's an example of a simple document with a TOC:
```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{hyperref}

\begin{document}
\tableofcontents

\section{Introduction}
Some text about the introduction.

\subsection{Subsection 1}
More text about subsection 1.

\subsection{Subsection 2}
Even more text about subsection 2.

\section{Conclusion}
The conclusion of the document.
\end{document}
```
In this example, the `hyperref` package is used to create links between the sections, subsections, and the table of contents. To generate the TOC, simply add `\tableofcontents` after the document class (here, `\documentclass{article}`). When you compile the document, a table of contents will appear automatically before the main content.

You can customize the appearance of the TOC using the `tocloft` package. For example, to change the font size of section headings, you can add the following line before the `\tableofcontents` command:
```latex
\renewcommand\cftsecfont{\Huge}
```
This will set the font size of section headings to "Huge." You can replace "Huge" with any other font size provided by LaTeX, such as "Large," "Normal," or "Small."

